HEADWORD: Arrected
<hw>Ar*rect"ed</hw>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>arrectus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>arrigere</ets>
to raise, erect; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>regere</ets> to lead straight, to
direct.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lifted up; raised; erect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attentive, as a person listening.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God speaks not the idle and unconcerned hearer, but to the
vigilant and <qex>arrect</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Smalridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arrect</ent>⟦br⟧
